# stripe — credentials (copy to $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/stripe/credentials.env,
# default ~/.config/stripe/credentials.env, and fill). This is the tier-3
# (user config) source in the 4-tier cascade:
#   flags > project .env(.local) > THIS user config > process env.
# A consuming project can override per-project by setting this in its own .env.
# PUBLIC REPO: never commit real values. Leave blank here; fill only the copy.

# Stripe secret API key (sk_live_… or sk_test_…) — every authenticated call uses
# it. Read-only use only; a restricted read-only key from the Stripe Dashboard
# (Developers → API keys) is sufficient and safer. Prefer config/env over the
# --api-key flag so the secret never touches the command line.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
